# Verbosity Roadmap — Unratified Content Files

## Purpose

This document tracks the pedagogical verbosity level of each content file and identifies what updates each file needs to reach consensus with the site's expanded content standard. The target verbosity level follows the golden ratio expansion principle: each file should carry enough pedagogical scaffolding — worked examples, historical analogies, reader-facing scenarios, and contextual bridging — to match the depth established in the top-tier analytical files.

## Verbosity Tiers

The site organizes content into three natural verbosity tiers based on purpose:

| Tier | Word Range | Purpose | Target |
|------|-----------|---------|--------|
| **Tier 3: Comprehensive** | 1,200-2,100+ | Deep analytical content, pivotal articles, multi-order analysis | Already at target |
| **Tier 2: Substantial** | 700-1,200 | Single-article deep dives, policy arguments, evidence pages | Expand to 1,000-1,600 |
| **Tier 1: Entry** | 300-700 | Introductory content, reference articles, action tools | Expand to 500-1,000 |

